</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="596" pageNumber="597">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="596" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pomona">Amara pomona</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 301. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="«California»">&quot;California&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation). Lectotype [as typus] (♂), designated by Hieke (1993: 112), in USNM [# 47294]. Synonymy established by Hieke (1993: 111).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="596" pageNumber="597">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="596" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vigilax">Amara vigilax</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 301. Type locality: &quot;near San Francisco [San Francisco County], California&quot; (original citation). Lectotype [as typus] (♀), designated by Hieke (1993: 112), in USNM [# 47295]. Synonymy established by Hieke (1993: 111).
</paragraph>
