<subSubSection pageId="596" pageNumber="597" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="596" pageNumber="597">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="596" pageNumber="597">This species ranges from northern Washington south to the Mexican border in southern California, east to eastern Nevada (Hieke 1993: 114). One specimen simply labeled from Mexico is known (Hieke 1993: 114).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
